The Verdant Depths lie deep beyond the Forest of Confusion.
The trees are not separate organisms but nodes in a single interconnected root network spanning the entire region.
Damage to one tree triggers responses hundreds of paces away within minutes. The forest has distributed intelligence, not thought.

Three functional aspects govern the woodland:
  Growth (Rootmother) - aggressive expansion that splits stone, smothers competing vegetation, converts dead matter to biomass.
  Decay (Blightwood) - recycling force that actively seeks dying tissue, intensified beyond normal decomposition.
  Predation (Thornfang) - the forest's immune system. Wolves, cats, spiders, serpents optimized into territorial enforcers.

Three Heartwood Guardians embody this triad: Rootmother builds, Blightwood Ancient recycles, Thornfang Alpha eliminates.
They are the forest's concentrated immune response to centuries of external threat.

The Forest of Confusion surrounding the Depths is the outermost defense: deliberate disorientation maintained by chemical signaling and deteriorating druidic quarantine wards.
The confusion is the canopy's first warning to intruders.
